WEBVTT

00:00.967 --> 00:02.958
<i>Previously on</i> One Tree Hill.

00:03.036 --> 00:04.162
Nathan, don't!

00:04.237 --> 00:07.434
I know that you saved my life.
And I'm gonna find a way to thank you.

00:07.507 --> 00:09.737
I swam into the car and I got trapped.

00:09.809 --> 00:11.868
I didn't save anybody.
Somebody saved me.

00:11.945 --> 00:13.572
- Who?
- Keith.

00:13.646 --> 00:16.638
- What did you say?
- Keith's dead, Peyton.

00:16.716 --> 00:18.274
The boys in Tree Hill are so boring.

00:18.351 --> 00:20.945
Isn't there anybody our age
you think you could fall for?

00:21.021 --> 00:22.113
Maybe.

00:22.188 --> 00:24.679
- Hey, Ma, are you pregnant?
- Yes, I am.

00:24.758 --> 00:28.717
Deb, you need to get back into rehab
or I will dissolve our partnership.

00:28.795 --> 00:31.593
I was thinking maybe the Ravens
could use another shooting guard.

00:31.664 --> 00:33.131
I'm putting him on the team.

00:33.199 --> 00:34.860
- What made you decide?
- You did.

00:34.934 --> 00:36.925
Looks like I'm not the only one
who knows you killed me.

00:37.003 --> 00:39.335
Shut up, you little smart-ass ghost.

00:39.406 --> 00:41.203
You're definitely pregnant.

00:44.511 --> 00:45.569
I was trying to call you.

00:45.645 --> 00:47.670
You mean, when you weren't
hanging out with Peyton?

00:48.381 --> 00:50.781
As far as I am concerned,
this friendship is over.

00:50.850 --> 00:53.717
I feel like I'm hanging onto
the two of us for you.

00:53.787 --> 00:57.416
If you've been listening to my podcasts,
then you know a lot about me.

00:57.490 --> 00:59.185
But did you know I had a brother?

00:59.259 --> 01:00.453
Are you Peyton?

01:00.527 --> 01:02.256
I guess I'm your brother.

01:06.332 --> 01:11.531
<i>You ever look at a picture of yourself</i>
<i>and see a stranger in the background?</i>

01:11.604 --> 01:14.767
<i>It makes you wonder,</i>
<i>how many strangers have pictures of you?</i>

01:14.841 --> 01:19.301
Yeah, it figures the first time a cheerleader
talks to me, we're related.

01:19.379 --> 01:22.678
- I haven't actually talked yet.
- Well, you just did.

01:24.250 --> 01:27.686
So this is a lot better than the other day
when you slammed the door in my face.

01:27.754 --> 01:30.416
- After you hung up on me when I called?
- You caught me off guard.

01:30.490 --> 01:32.981
And you think I was expecting you
to show up on my front porch?

01:33.059 --> 01:35.357
According to your podcast, yes.

01:36.663 --> 01:40.724
I've known about you for a while now.
But, I didn't know if I wanted to meet you.

01:40.800 --> 01:45.430
So when you called, it freaked me out.
But I was curious.

01:45.505 --> 01:47.496
Why didn't you just call me back?

01:47.574 --> 01:49.633
I was afraid you'd hang up on me.

01:51.478 --> 01:53.571
I'm sorry. Okay, look.

01:54.314 --> 01:59.377
Let's start over. Hi, I'm Derek.
I guess I'm your brother.

02:00.687 --> 02:03.850
Hi, Derek. I'm Peyton.

02:03.923 --> 02:06.653
So, Peyton, who'd you bring?

02:07.026 --> 02:09.586
- What do you mean?
- Well, you don't strike me as a dumb girl.

02:09.662 --> 02:13.496
So, who'd you bring as backup
in case I turned out to be a psycho?

02:17.303 --> 02:20.704
Derek, Lucas. Lucas, Derek.

02:22.842 --> 02:24.241
That guy seems really cool.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.107
I mean,
you throw a skirt on him and he's you.

02:26.179 --> 02:27.510
We are not that much alike.

02:27.580 --> 02:30.640
Oh, no. No. He's a photographer.
You're an artist.

02:30.717 --> 02:33.550
You wouldn't shut the hell up
about that damn Mozella album.

02:33.620 --> 02:36.783
You both ordered the same breakfast.
I mean, I thought that was cute.

02:36.856 --> 02:39.723
We ordered scrambled eggs and toast,
same as you, same as everybody else.

02:39.792 --> 02:40.850
It was the freaking special.

02:40.927 --> 02:42.360
Okay, you know what? I quit.

02:42.428 --> 02:44.896
You have absolutely nothing
in common with your brother.

02:44.964 --> 02:47.489
I just don't know if I wanna do it anymore.

02:47.567 --> 02:50.593
Get close to somebody
so they can leave again.

02:50.670 --> 02:53.332
Look, on the contrary of what may
be written on your wall,

02:53.406 --> 02:55.374
people don't always leave.

02:55.441 --> 02:57.500
All right? I mean,
last time I checked, I'm still here.

02:57.577 --> 03:00.546
So is Nathan, Haley, Brooke.
Okay, maybe not Brooke, but...

03:00.613 --> 03:02.808
- Yeah, I think she wishes we would leave.
- Yeah.

03:02.882 --> 03:05.373
Have you heard from her?

03:05.451 --> 03:07.749
Not since she broke up with me.

03:07.820 --> 03:11.916
Well, get your game face on
and talk to her. It's playoff time.

03:11.991 --> 03:14.516
Everybody should be in a good mood.

03:16.229 --> 03:20.393
I need to be tutored.
I think I'm failing marriage.

03:22.168 --> 03:24.762
Did you try sleeping with the teacher?

03:27.307 --> 03:29.935
So, what's gotten into you?

03:30.009 --> 03:32.000
I'm just tired of thinking
about the accident.

03:32.078 --> 03:35.605
I need to get focused again
and start thinking about basketball.

03:36.249 --> 03:38.308
- All right.
- And you.

03:38.384 --> 03:40.181
You really are failing marriage, aren't you?

03:40.253 --> 03:43.017
You know I'm always thinking
about you, Hales.

03:43.089 --> 03:46.456
Thank you for being so patient with me.
I just needed some time.

03:46.526 --> 03:50.826
But after tonight,
everything's gonna be better. I promise.

03:50.897 --> 03:52.762
I'm really glad to see you so happy.

03:52.832 --> 03:55.323
But I just don't know if everything
that happened to you on the bridge

03:55.401 --> 03:57.369
is gonna go away so quickly.

03:57.437 --> 04:00.304
You know,
no matter what goes wrong in my life,

04:00.373 --> 04:04.366
every time I set foot on that
basketball court, it all goes away.

04:05.545 --> 04:06.773
You'll see.

04:09.449 --> 04:10.541
All right?

04:17.322 --> 04:20.349
- You nervous?
- No.

04:20.426 --> 04:23.759
- You lying?
- Yeah.

04:27.100 --> 04:29.227
Remember my first game as a Raven?

04:30.003 --> 04:32.733
Yeah. You played like crap.

04:33.740 --> 04:36.004
I remember walking around
for a whole week talking about,

04:36.075 --> 04:38.168
"Man, I gotta take me a Lucas."

04:38.778 --> 04:43.408
Look, the point is,
I let too much get to my head. You know?

04:43.483 --> 04:48.284
I mean, basketball is basketball
whether it's on the River Court or in here.

04:49.656 --> 04:51.521
You remember that and you'll be all right.

04:51.591 --> 04:54.719
Yeah, I'd be better
if you was out there with me though.

04:55.094 --> 04:59.690
Well, I will be, sort of.

05:04.437 --> 05:07.429
- Wait, this is your jersey.
- Not anymore.

05:14.881 --> 05:16.371
Thanks, man.

05:18.785 --> 05:21.049
- Did you wash it?
- Oh, man.

05:25.458 --> 05:28.256
Man, I'm gonna make this place look good.

05:31.297 --> 05:32.696
This jersey, too.

05:32.765 --> 05:36.064
You better. It ain't used to looking bad.

